  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing the Application Scope**\n\nI\'m now diving into the user\'s request. My focus is on understanding the nature of the React application\'s structure. I\'m taking the initial step of analyzing the provided information, which includes images and descriptive text. I am determining the key features of the application, such as its nature as a trucking/logistical/journey app for a truck driver.\n\n\n**Defining the Initial Screen**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the first screen: the Home/Check-In page. I am prioritizing displaying \"Jo\303\243o Silva\'s\" photo in the header. I have exact URLs to choose from and am deciding on the best one to use or if a generated version is preferable.\n\n\n**Visualizing the Driver\'s Interface**\n\nNow, I\'m forming a clearer visual concept for the driver\'s home screen. I\'m prioritizing the integration of \"JO\303\203O SILVA\'s\" photo in the header. I\'m focusing on the green \"ONLINE\" pulse indicator. I also envision the status card with its text variations (\"Voc\303\252 est\303\241 fora de jornada\" or \"Voc\303\252 est\303\241 em jornada\") and appropriate icons. A prominent, pulsing \"CHECK-IN\" or \"CHECK-OUT\" button is central, along with location details.\n\n\n**Structuring the Mileage Input**\n\nI\'m now detailing the \"Active Journey\" screen. I\'m focusing on the input for mileage, considering its placement and accompanying components. I\'m considering inputs for \"Odometer\", along with quick-select buttons for various stop/start reasons like \"CARGA,\" \"DESCARGA,\" \"DESCANSO,\" and \"QUEBRA\". Then the journey status screen has to show \"EM JORNADA\" and include \"ESTADIA ATIVA\" subtitle. I have to think about visual indicators, such as a large chronometer display. The screen also incorporates location details, like \"Posto Graal\".\n\n\n\n**Designing the \"Active Journey\" Screen**\n\nI\'m now detailing the \"Active Journey\" screen\'s final elements. A \"CHECK-OUT\" button, colored red with a logout icon, is essential. Below this, I visualize a summary card, displaying the selected \"MOTIVO,\" the entered \"OD\303\224METRO,\" and the journey\'s start time. I am now transitioning to the profile section.\n\n**Constructing the Driver Profile**\n\nI\'m now designing the profile screen, focusing on data organization. I will have a \"Dados do Motorista\" section, including name, CPF, and CNH. I also will build a \"Dados do Ve\303\255culo\" section that will feature Scania R500 truck. Then the profile has a \"Sair da Conta\" button. I am considering the use of dark mode using the \"High-Visibility Logistical Dark\" design tokens. I want to build a stellar, premium React experience with consistent branding. I think I will use Tailwind CSS. I have now decided to use lucide-react icons instead of material design.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Icon Selection**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the icon selection for the application. It\'s critical I avoid custom SVG icons, sticking with `lucide-react` instead. I\'m focusing on the perfect equivalents for each use case, cross-referencing and choosing the best-fit options, such as `Moon` for \"moon,\" `PlayCircle` for \"play_circle,\" and `LogOut` for \"logout.\" My current focus is to refine the choices for \"hotel,\" \"build,\" and others.\n\n\n**Defining the Screen Architecture**\n\nI\'ve just recognized a critical design shift. Initially, I thought this was a single-screen app, but it\'s not; it\'s a multi-tab application! I\'m now designing a single-page application with three tabs: \"In\303\255cio,\" \"Hist\303\263rico,\" and \"Perfil\". The \"In\303\255cio\" tab will have two states: \"Fora de Jornada\" and \"Em Jornada.\" This structure fully addresses the user\'s intent.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will start by viewing the `metadata.json` file to check its contents and see if I need to update the application name and description."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 13
      nanos: 835819172
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
