    thinking: "**Envisioning App Structure**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the app\'s structure, thinking I can build the whole thing in `src/App.tsx` with animations and state management. The plan is to introduce a mock database for starters, and feed it some initial historical data that matches the screenshot exactly. I\'ve started defining an initial entry with ID 1 and the name \"Posto Graal Petrop.\"\n\n\n**Adding Initial Data**\n\nI\'ve added initial data entries to the mock database, including an entry for \"Porto de Santos\" with ID 2. I\'m focusing on persisting these to `localStorage` now, ensuring that user edits and filters are saved across reloads. I\'ve also incorporated driver profile details: Name, Full Name, CPF, CNH, and an avatar URL. I plan to seamlessly incorporate this data into the component state.\n\n\n**Defining Truck and Journey**\n\nI\'m now integrating truck and journey details. I\'ve defined the truck model as Scania R500, with its corresponding image URL and license plates. I\'ve also incorporated an `isOnline` status, which can be toggled. Furthermore, I\'ve outlined the active journey state, including `checkedIn`, `startTime`, `location`, `reason`, and `odometer`, all set by default and persisted too. I\'m aiming for dynamic additions to these data points now.\n\n\n**Implementing Journey Tracking**\n\nI\'m now implementing the journey tracking logic. I\'ve defined how `activeJourney` is updated when checking in: setting `checkedIn` to true, capturing the start time with a formatted string, and storing the reason, odometer reading, and location details. Also, on check-out, I\'ve outlined the logic to format a new `HistoryEntry` and display a success message to the user.\n\n\n"
