  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Refining Data Structures**\n\nI\'m currently updating the `App.tsx` file to align the `INITIAL_HISTORY` data structure with the new `HistoryEntry` type. Specifically, I\'m working on ensuring the initial history object matches the updated interface, particularly the `location` field.\n\n\n**Updating Data Structures**\n\nI\'ve just revised the `INITIAL_HISTORY` data structure in `App.tsx` once again. I\'m focusing on incorporating more detailed information into each history entry, such as `startTime`, `endTime`, `durationHoursNum`, `hourlyRate`, and `totalAmount`, as well as location, date, duration, and type of activity. My goal is to represent all activities as accurately as possible within each `HistoryEntry`.\n\n\n**Refining Mock Data**\n\nI\'m now focusing on ensuring that all entries within the mock history are correctly designated as either \"CARGA\" or \"DESCARGA,\" aligning with the user\'s specific requirement for check-in and check-out logs related to loading and unloading. This refinement is critical for accurately simulating the application\'s expected behavior. I have updated the mock history data to reflect this, ensuring each entry aligns with the user\'s focus on these specific activity types. The `INITIAL_JOURNEY` and related check-in/out functions have also been updated to align.\n\n\n**Implementing Check-Out Logic**\n\nI\'m currently integrating the check-out functionality. I\'m focusing on crafting the `handleCheckOut` function. I\'m calculating duration, formatting the end time, and determining the total amount based on the duration and hourly rate from the active journey. This data will be assembled into a `HistoryEntry` and added. I want to ensure this updates the UI as well.\n\n\n**Designing Report Generation**\n\nI\'m now designing the report generation feature, specifically the \"Relat\303\263rio de Cobran\303\247a de Estadia\". The idea is that clicking a \"CARGA\" or \"DESCARGA\" entry in `HistoricoTab.tsx` will trigger either a modal or a dedicated tab. This display will include a professional report titled \"RELAT\303\223RIO DE PERMAN\303\212NCIA E COBRAN\303\207A,\" detailing driver data and other relevant details, such as staying time and cost.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will update `App.tsx` with log entries geared around Carga/Descarga locations, hours of stay, charging rates, and calculated amounts, replacing odometer fields. I will also adapt the check-in and check-out handlers to manage these location-based and billing parameters."
