  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Billing Options**\n\nOkay, I\'m now focusing on the first billing option, \"Valor Combinado por Hora.\" I\'ve got the calculation down: duration in hours times the hourly rate. The tricky part comes in when \"Desconsiderar as 5 primeiras horas\" is checked; that requires subtracting five hours from the total duration before the calculation. I\'m working on clarifying the logic for this part.\n\n\n**Clarifying Legal Calculations**\n\nI\'ve been examining the legal billing option tied to ANTT Resolution 11.442/2007. The core calculation of R$ 2.50 per ton/hour for exceeding the initial 5 hours is clear. I\'ve now clarified the edge case where the \"disregard the first 5 hours\" setting is OFF, potentially calculating from the very first hour. This introduces flexibility for the user in different scenarios, and I\'m updating the logic accordingly to make it configurable as requested.\n\n\n**Designing UI Components**\n\nI\'m now designing the user interface elements. I\'ve broken down the options into clear components. First, there\'s a \"Forma de C\303\241lculo\" selector: either \"Combinado por Hora\" or \"Conforme a Lei (ANTT)\". Next, a \"Desconsiderar as 5 primeiras horas (toler\303\242ncia legal)\" toggle, with a true/false value, which is crucial for handling the \"disregard the first 5 hours\" logic for both calculation methods. This makes the UI intuitive and flexible.\n\n\n"
